{"author":{"id":"2b4457b01effb9c8da29ce6d2aafea7e87f3ee3dadec9f9fc646e1c6838f70dd"},"ops":[{"type":6,"timestamp":1580152580,"nonce":"eEbRDGx7ajXspu3x/CL4sCqCLbU=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdDM0NDQwMDIwNA=="},"target":"996b3603f99c10dea6ac561f981eebe4e4981a7efa87b8d7077fbbddaacdeadb","message":"The current version (snippy-4.4.5+galaxy1, 32f2211eeec3) of [snippy](https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/blob/master/tools/snippy/snippy.xml) doesn't handle sample names in a way that is consistent with snippy-core.\n\nThe element_identifier of outputs are being set using `${tool.name} on ${on_string}`, (as many other tools do). This results in alignment files where all samples are named `snippy`.\n\n```\n\u003eReference\nCTAGTCAGATCGATG...\n\u003esnippy\nCTGATCTAGCATGA...\n\u003esnippy\nCTAGCTGATGCTGTA...\n\u003esnippy\nCGATGCTAGCGATG...\n```\n\nSince multiple sequences have the same name in the alignment file, downstream tools (like `iqtree`) can't process the file.","files":null}]}